                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="48029" author="pjones" created="Mon, 19 Nov 2012 18:40:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47297" author="utopiabound" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 12:01:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;master: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4448&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4448&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also created &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2261&quot; title=&quot;Add cache stats to zfs osd&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2261&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2261&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; enhancement to add caching stats to osd-zfs&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47291" author="adilger" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 09:27:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If the problem is understood, then all that is needed is to skip the test case for ZFS, checking $(facet_fstype ost1) == ZFS, with a comment explaining why, and referencing this bug. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47266" author="utopiabound" created="Thu, 1 Nov 2012 16:28:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The osd code for ZFS code does not count cache hits, misses or accesses.  Adding that all cache accesses are misses will still cause test 156 to fail since it expects cache_hits to increase when readcache is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this really a blocker? Should it be recharacterized as a feature enhancement to add read/write cache stats to ZFS?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46781" author="adilger" created="Fri, 19 Oct 2012 12:31:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Li Wei, in the future can you please include more of the test output details of the test failure.  Otherwise it is more difficult to understand the problem and do bug triage than needed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46646" author="liwei" created="Tue, 16 Oct 2012 21:43:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prompted to Blocker for 2.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46612" author="liwei" created="Tue, 16 Oct 2012 00:25:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1813180e-172c-11e2-afe1-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1813180e-172c-11e2-afe1-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="46246" author="liwei" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 09:56:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9d098640-11fc-11e2-a663-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9d098640-11fc-11e2-a663-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="45213" author="yujian" created="Wed, 19 Sep 2012 07:34:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lustre Build: &lt;a href=&quot;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_3/19&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-b2_3/19&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
